<p style="text-align:justify;">but the low points of land near the water are frequently shaded by groves of venerable Oak and Elm.</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">The soil of the Plains is a mixture of Sand, Clay, Gravel and Stones in many places, but the glen where in the river runs is a mixture of Clay and black mould.</p>
